<h1>Problem 1173 - 2010 IMO, P4 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(P\) be a point interior to triangle \(ABC\) (with \(CA \neq CB\)). The lines \(AP\), \(BP\) and \(CP\) meet again its circumcircle \(\Gamma\) at \(K\), \(L\), respectively \(M\). The tangent line at \(C\) to \(\Gamma\) meets the line \(AB\) at \(S\). Suppose that \(SC = SP\). Prove that \(MK = ML\).</p>
